{% block content %}
  <h2>Why we are doing this</h2>
  <p>In 2023 the Robinson Huron Treaty First Nations reached a ten billion dollar settlement for unpaid annuities, covering all 21 signatory communities. The money has flowed to the communities, but many members across the treaty have said the same thing: we do not have a clear picture of how the funds are governed, what the rules are, or what we are entitled to see. These concerns are already public and shared widely. This Circle exists to turn that shared concern into clear, respectful, member-led questions.</p>

  <h2>What we are, and are not</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We are members and beneficiaries, organizing across communities as one voice.</li>
    <li>We are independent. We are not a band council committee, and we are not part of the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund or any community's administration. Those are the bodies we ask questions of, so our independence is the point.</li>
    <li>We are non-partisan. This is about transparency and member information, not about removing or attacking any leader.</li>
    <li>We work from sourced facts and we ask questions. We do not make accusations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Principles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Member-led and beneficiary-focused.</li>
    <li>Sourced facts, framed as questions. No accusations, and no naming of private individuals.</li>
    <li>Respectful of each community's own governance and the right of members to information.</li>
    <li>Independent of councils, the Litigation Fund, and any tribal organization.</li>
    <li>Open to any member of a Robinson Huron Treaty First Nation who shares these principles.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How it works, to start</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A small core team to coordinate, with at least one contact per participating community.</li>
    <li>An informal working group for now. If it grows and needs to hold funds or retain shared resources, we will formalize then.</li>
    <li>Decisions by consensus of the core team where possible.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>First deliverables</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>A one-page shared members' transparency standard, the common list of questions, ready for members in any community to use.</li>
    <li>A joint letter to the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund requesting the disbursement agreement, the trustee list, and the beneficiary reporting members can expect.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="card">
    <p class="muted">This page is a draft for discussion. Sources for the background facts: public reporting on the 2023 Robinson Huron Treaty settlement and the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund's trustee and disbursement structure.</p>
